    "description": "Human glucokinase is a cytoplasmic enzyme that uses ATP to phosphorylate glucose imported into the cell to glucose 6-phosphate in glycolysis. It is classified as a glucokinase (EC 2.7.1.2) rather than a hexokinase (EC 2.7.1.1) on the basis of its substrate specificity: the enzyme shows much greater activity with glucose than with either mannose or galactose, and no activity with fructose. It is located in hepatacytes and pancreatic beta cells and important in maintaining the cells' glucose homeostasis.",
